CNCP v1 23429
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12136: `<component>` of void element with content causes hydration mismatch",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:05.492068+00:00",
  "text": "`<component>` of void element with content causes hydration mismatch\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.11\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#__SSR__\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nReproduction contains an example where a component called ContentNode references itself while rendering a tree of content elements. When enabling SSR, hydration mismatches are reported, but when comparing the generated HTML, everything seems OK.\n\n### What is expected?\n\nNo hydration mismatches.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nHydration mismatches are reported.\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
